{"abstract": "The change is a strategy shift at MSNBC, which long has filled its schedule with left-leaning political commentary and now is moving toward straight news from 9 a.m. until 3 p.m.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/20/business/media/msnbc-removes-two-hosts-to-focus-on-straight-news.html", "snippet": "The change is a strategy shift at MSNBC, which long has filled its schedule with left-leaning political commentary and now is moving toward straight news from 9 a.m. until 3 p.m.", "lead_paragraph": "Facing weak ratings for its afternoon shows, MSNBC is shaking up its daytime schedule to focus on straight news coverage. The cable news network said on Thursday that it was canceling its 1 p.m. broadcast hosted by Ronan Farrow, as well as its 2 p.m. broadcast hosted by Joy-Ann Reid. In their place will be a two-hour block of news with Thomas Roberts, host of MSNBC\u2019s \u201cWay Too Early\u201d at 5:30 a.m. Ms. Reid will work as a national correspondent, and Mr. Farrow, the 27-year-old son of Mia Farrow and Woody Allen, will work on a series of prime time specials and interviews. The change is a strategy shift at MSNBC, which long has filled its schedule with left-leaning political commentary and now is moving toward straight news from 9 a.m. until 3 p.m. ", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "2", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [], "headline": {"main": "MSNBC Removes Two Hosts to Focus on Straight News", "kicker": "Business Briefing", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "MSNBC Removes Two Hosts to Focus on Straight News", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "organizations", "value": "MSNBC", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "News and News Media", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}], "pub_date": "2015-02-20T00:48:08+0000", "document_type": "article", "news_desk": "Business", "section_name": "Business Day", "subsection_name": "Media", "byline": {"original": "By Emily Steel", "person": [{"firstname": "Emily", "middlename": null, "lastname": "Steel", "qualifier": null, "title": null, "role": "reported", "organization": "", "rank": 1}], "organization": null}, "type_of_material": "Brief", "_id": "nyt://article/ba5f4de0-f709-5b95-b6b4-d1aabe2c1d7c", "word_count": 134, "uri": "nyt://article/ba5f4de0-f709-5b95-b6b4-d1aabe2c1d7c"}
